15: By default, there is a sendmail running on this jail, which sends all non-local
16: E-Mail through a smart-host at 127.0.1.1, which is where the mail-jail is
17: located. If you want to install your own mail server on the jail, you can
18: install your favourite Mailer daemon from the ports. Don't forget to read the
19: section about ports and sendmail in the FreeBSD handbook. Another possibility is
20: to change the sendmail configuration residing in /etc/mail to your liking.
21: In order to disable sendmail entirely, please read the rc.conf(5) manpage and
22: afterwards add sendmail_enable="NONE" to your rc.conf. Setting sendmail_enable
23: to "NO" will not enable sendmail entirely but will have a local-only daemon
24: running. The mail jail will at some later point receive a setup which will make
25: separate mail servers in the personal jails unnecessary.
